      <!-- Selection Guide -->
      <h2 id="selection-guide" class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-heading text-navy mb-4">How to Select the Right Industrial Centrifuge</h2>
      <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Centrifuge selection depends on five primary process parameters. Answering these questions enables Dolphin&apos;s engineers to recommend the optimal machine and configuration for your specific application.</p>

      <div class="bg-white rounded-xl border border-gray-200 p-6 shadow-sm mb-8">
        <ol class="space-y-4 text-text-light">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="bg-gold text-navy font-bold w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-sm">1</span>
            <span><strong class="text-navy">What phases are present?</strong> Liquid&ndash;liquid (oil + water), liquid&ndash;solid (one liquid phase with solids), or three-phase (oil + water + solids)? This determines purifier vs clarifier vs three-phase separator.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="bg-gold text-navy font-bold w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-sm">2</span>
            <span><strong class="text-navy">What is the solids concentration?</strong> Below 5% by volume favors a disc stack; above 10% requires a decanter. The transition zone (5&ndash;10%) requires evaluation of both options.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="bg-gold text-navy font-bold w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-sm">3</span>
            <span><strong class="text-navy">What is the required flow rate?</strong> Disc stack models range from 1 GPM to 70+ GPM. Decanters can handle much higher solids volumes at lower liquid flow rates.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="bg-gold text-navy font-bold w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-sm">4</span>
            <span><strong class="text-navy">What are the fluid properties?</strong> Viscosity, density differential between phases, and operating temperature all affect centrifuge sizing and may require pre-heating.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="bg-gold text-navy font-bold w-7 h-7 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center shrink-0 text-sm">5</span>
            <span><strong class="text-navy">What is the operating environment?</strong> Hazardous area (ATEX/explosion-proof), food-grade (3-A sanitary), marine (Lloyd&apos;s Register, DNV), or standard industrial?</span>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <p class="text-text-light leading-relaxed mb-4">For a structured selection process, see our <a href="/alfa-laval-centrifuge-selection-guide/" class="text-navy font-semibold hover:text-gold transition-colors">Industrial Centrifuge Selection Guide</a>. For complex applications, Dolphin offers paid sample testing at our Warren, Michigan facility &mdash; ship us a sample of your fluid and we will run it through multiple centrifuge configurations to determine the optimal centrifuge type and settings for your application.</p>

